@node TRANS "Settings: Transporters"

  Very simple, I hope. First select a definition slot number (1-20).
  Then use the SET button. Click left on a transporter for the start
  position and repeat it and click right to set the destination position.

  All transporter settings will be check to have start and destination
  position set. And that there is really a transporter field on both
  positions. Of course you may have transporter fields with no action.
  That's very interesting: find a working transporter out of many
  transporter fields...

  Click on DEL to clear the current definition slot, or DELALL to erase
  all definitions. With USE THIS you get back to the main settings.

@endnode
@node BADDY "Settings: Baddy homes"

  The button in the first line defines if baddies are able to create
  normal field out of empty fields (=YES) or not (=OFF). Use this
  careful or your levels will become very easy.

  In the second line you define the positions of all baddy homes. Here
  your baddies appear and starts to move. First select a definition slot
  number (1-24). Then click on SET and in the edit area click on a normal
  field to place a baddy home.

  Click on DEL to clear the current definition slot, or DELALL to erase
  all definitions. With USE THIS you get back to the main settings.

@endnode
@node WARPS "Settings: Warp fields"

  Here you define level warpes to any level. Again select a definition
  slot number (1-4). Then use the SET button to place a warp field on
  any field type.

  In the second line you define, if you have to collect all diamonds
  before the warps are available (=DIAMONDS COLLECTED) or if they are
  available when entering the level (=ALWAYS FROM START).

  Click on DEL to clear the current definition slot, or DELALL to erase
  all definitions. With USE THIS you get back to the main settings.

@endnode
